<p>Alleged prohibited distribution in Thailand of the film &#8220;Shakespeare Must Die&#8221; 
produced by Mr. Manit Sriwanichpoom and written and directed by Ms. Smanrat 
Kanjanavanit. According to information received, on 3 April 2012, the Third Committee 
of Film and Video Censorship Board issued a banning order prohibiting the distribution 
of the movie, which is as adaptation in Thai-language of William Shakespeare&#8217;s 
Macbeth. It is alleged that the Censorship Board deemed that the movie &#8220;has content 
</p>
<p>that causes disunity among the people of the nation&#8221;, and that the filmmakers did not 
</p>
<p>agree to re-shoot the scenes that were the subject of the Third Committee&#8217;s various 
objections. It is alleged that the banning of the film is politically motivated. 
