<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged closing down of the Al Misbah Ahmadi mosque in the city of Bekasi, West 
Java, Indonesia. According to the information received, on 14 February 2013, the 
Administration of the city of Bekasi placed a sign in front of the Al Misbah mosque 
prohibiting any activities from being conducted there. In May 2013, members of the 
Public Order Agency reportedly locked the gates of the mosque leaving several 
members of Ahmadi congregation trapped inside for several hours. On 4 April 2013, 
members of the Public Order Agency allegedly installed a fence around the mosque 
preventing the Ahmadi congregation from carrying out religious activities there.  
