<p><b>Torture;  </b> 
</p>
<p>Alleged removal from his cell and isolation of detained human rights defender, Mr 
Rajab, Director of the Bahrain Centre for Human Rights, President of the Gulf Centre 
for Human Rights and Deputy Secretary General of the International Federation for 
Human Rights (FIDH).  According to the information received, Mr Nabeel Rajab was 
removed from his cell after having witnessed acts of torture committed by prison staff 
against fellow prisoners.  He was reportedly also denied access to his relatives and legal 
representation. Mr. Rajab was the subject of previous communications (see 
A/HRC/22/67, case no BHR 6/2012). 
