<p>Allegations of threats against human rights defenders contained in a statement made by 
Thailand&#8217;s Deputy Prime Minister prior to the 2nd Asia-Pacific Water Summit. 
According to the information received, on 12 May 2013, Mr. Plodprasop Suraswadi, 
Thailand&#8217;s Deputy Prime Minister, reportedly gave a media interview prior to the 2nd 
Asia-Pacific Water Summit in Chiang Mai from 14 to 20 May 2013, warning 
environmental activists, water-resources activists, and other members of civil society 
that they would be arrested if they protested at the Summit. 
