</b></p>
<p><b>Myanmar;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations of violations of the right to freedom of religion or belief and freedom of 
opinion and expression of a monk teaching the doctrine of an alternative Buddhist order.  
According to information received, U Ottama is imprisoned in Taunggyi Prison, Shan 
State, Myanmar for reportedly teaching a doctrine known as Moepyar. On 3 October 
2012, the Kalaw Township Court in Shan State charged him with violating Section 
295A of the Penal Code for insulting religion, and sentenced him to two years&#8217; 
imprisonment.  On 19 February 2013, the Taunggyi District Court and Shan State High 
Court reportedly dismissed the appeal without a hearing, and the matter is now pending 
before the Supreme Court.      
</p>
<p>26/07/2013 </p>

